## The "Click Click Website" flow

The category-creating capability. Paste an Airbnb URL, get a working booking-capable website in under 5 minutes. Nobody else does this — Lodgify is closest at hours-to-days, Hostaway/Hostfully require sales calls, Mews is 6-12 weeks.

### How it works (built today)

Channex is one of Airbnb's certified Connectivity Partners. GAS uses Channex's official OAuth flow — not scraping.

1. **Click 1 — Connect Airbnb** — `POST /api/admin/channex/:connId/airbnb/connect`. Generates OAuth token, calls Channex's `getAirbnbConnectionLink`, returns Airbnb OAuth URL. User authorises in Airbnb → Channex creates channel → callback to GAS persists channel ID.
2. **Pick listing** — `GET /api/admin/channex/channel/:id/airbnb/listings`.
3. **Import listing** — `POST /api/admin/channex/channel/:id/airbnb/import`. Pulls full `listing_details` from Channex (Airbnb's official data). Creates `properties`, `bookable_units`, `room_images`, `gas_sync_channel_mappings`. Strips Airbnb's `aki_policy` compression on image URLs → full-res photos. Account-scoped via connection (not client-supplied) for safety.
4. **Click 2 — Create Website** (Web Builder). Auto-populates all settings from imported data via standard defaults. Spins up multisite blog. Site live on `{slug}.sites.gas.travel`.

### Standard defaults that auto-populate (no user input needed)

| Setting | Source |
|---|---|
| Site title | `property.name` |
| Hero image | `room_images` where `is_primary = true` |
| Hero title | `property.name + ', ' + property.city` |
| Hero subtitle | First sentence of `bookable_unit.short_description` |
| Hero CTA | "Book now" → wired to booking widget |
| About text | `bookable_unit.full_description` |
| About image | Second non-primary `room_images` row |
| Rooms grid | Auto from `bookable_units` |
| Contact map | `property.latitude`, `property.longitude` |
| Contact address | `property.address`, `city`, `country` |
| Currency | `property.currency` (from Airbnb `pricing.listing_currency`) |
| Default language | English; auto-translate later |
| Meta title | `{property.name} | {city}` truncated to 60 chars |
| Meta description | First 155 chars of `short_description` |
| OG image | Same as hero image |
| Time zone | Derived from lat/lng |
| Check-in / out | 15:00 / 11:00 industry default |
| Theme | `gas-theme-developer-light` |
| Subdomain | `slugify(property.name) + '.sites.gas.travel'` |

User chooses **zero** settings to publish a working site. Settings are the *reward* of having a live site, not the *gate* to it. Reverses standard SaaS-onboarding.

### Day 2 steps (not required for first publish)

- Custom domain (via registrar reseller API — partner play, see Revenue Stack)
- Stripe Connect (already built — OAuth, no API keys)
- Additional languages (auto-translate via existing AI)
- Brand colour customisation
- Repuso/Revyoos widget code for reviews

### Why this is defensible

Anyone catching up has to build: Channex-level OAuth, multisite infrastructure, theme system, booking widget, content auto-derivation, smart defaults, image-URL high-res unpacking. Plus get through Airbnb's certified-partner program. Lodgify could in theory close the gap but their pricing model rewards slow funnels. Hostaway/Hostfully are moving upmarket. By the time anyone wakes up, GAS owns the brand line.

**The product line:** *"Connect your Airbnb. Click Create. Your website is live."*

