## Multi-CM unified-demand-side

SiteMinder / Channex unify the SUPPLY side — one CM connection → many OTAs.
GAS unifies the DEMAND side — one website → many CMs underneath.

Combined, GAS clients have full distribution flexibility in both directions. Nobody else offers both ends.

### What multi-CM-on-one-site unlocks

Three new product categories with no clean home today:

1. **Multi-property owners with mixed CMs** — hotel on Beds24, cottage on Hostaway; doesn't want to migrate either. Today they have two websites. With GAS, one site.
2. **Property management companies (PMCs)** — managing properties for different owners, each owner has their own CM contract. PMC needs a single branded site. Today they can't.
3. **Destination / consortium sites** — "Places to stay in Hebden Bridge", "Boutique hostels of the Cotswolds". Multiple independent operators, different CMs, pooled marketing under one site. Direct bookings, no OTA cut. **Potential product line: "GAS Destinations".**

### CM-coverage strategy

Every CM not supported = a customer who can't use the unified-site feature. CM-adapter breadth becomes a real competitive parameter.

| Tier | Provider | Role |
|---|---|---|
| **Entry (Tier 0)** | GAS CM (Channex-backed) | For hosts with no CM yet — the "click click website" entry |
| **Pro (Tier 1)** | Beds24, Hostaway, Hostfully | Direct integrations for operators with existing pro CM |
| **Pro Compatible (Tier 1.5)** | Smoobu, Lodgify (Calry-routed) | Smaller mid-tier CMs |
| **Scale / Long Tail (Tier 2)** | Channex multi-aggregation | Long-tail OTAs and CMs via Channex's certified ecosystem |

Same GAS surface, swap the CM underneath. The user doesn't see the difference.

### Marketing the CM strategy

Don't advertise GAS-the-CM as a Beds24/Hostaway competitor. Frame it as "for hosts who don't have a channel manager yet". Tells partners they're not being attacked. Tells Airbnb-only hosts they have an on-ramp.

**Brand line:** *"Bring your channel manager. Or none. Or several. Build one site that works with all of them."*

